laboratory_examinations.findings: No evidence of cancer in chest or upper abdomen; soft-tissue densities in the pelvis thought to be resolving postoperative inflammatory changes.

laboratory_examinations.procedure_name: CT scan of abdomen and pelvis
laboratory_examinations.findings: Occlusion of the inferior vena cava by a circumferential retroperitoneal soft-tissue mass measuring approximately 4 cm; two lesions in the liver approximately 5 mm in greatest dimension.

laboratory_examinations.date: 11 days after the previous CT scan
laboratory_examinations.findings: Marked FDG avidity in the retroperitoneal mass and liver lesions; liver lesions had increased in size and number since the previous CT scan.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Increased in size and number since previous imaging.

laboratory_examinations.findings: Aspartate aminotransferase level rose from 60 to 251 U per liter (reference range, 9 to 32), and bilirubin level rose from 0.4 to 2.1 mg per deciliter (reference range, 0.1 to 1.0).
